	<element name="Windwalker Armor" type="Magic Item" source="Homebrew" id="ID_CUSTOM_ITEM_WINDWALKER_ARMOR">
		<description>
			<p>The Windwalker Armor is a blue-gray suit of plate armor, though it does not have armor on the upper arms, nor a helmet. It is decorated with a set of ancient runes that describe various storms and winds. It enables bursts of speed in the wearer, enabling feats of jumping and climbing and even short, near-uncontrolled bursts of flight.</p>
			<p>This armor holds 6 charges. As long as a single charge remains, the armor is light and will not fatigue the wearer due to long marches, wearing it for extended periods, etc.</p>
			<p>A charge may be spent each round on for one of the following: </p>
			<p class="indent">During the wearer’s turn: Increase the wearer’s movement speed by 30 ft. Only usable if already moved more then 10ft that round. not usable while bound/... </p>
			<p class="indent">Gain advantage on an Athletics (strength) or Acrobatics (dexterity) ability check.</p>
			<p class="indent">The wearer moves 15 feet in any direction (including up). If this movement brings the wearer into contact with an enemy and they make an attack immediately after, the attack deals an additional 1d6 bludgeoning damage.</p>
			<p>The armor recovers 1 charge per short rest or all per long rest.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="keywords" />
			<set name="category">Magic Armor</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">0</set>
			<set name="weight" lb="0">0 lb.</set>
			<set name="slot">body</set>
			<set name="type" addition="heavy">Armor</set>
			<set name="rarity">uncommon</set>
			<set name="enhancement">0</set>
			<set name="armor">ID_INTERNAL_ARMOR_GROUP_HEAVY</set>
		</setters>
